            We want to see high-quality guidance and help being made available to CICs and to those who wish to set up CICs. This will of course help to encourage take-up of this new kind of company, which is what the Government want, and will make it easier for people to comply with their legal obligations. Good information is obviously very important so that people set up a CIC only if that is the right solution for them because when they do so they will be putting a permanent lock on their assets and profits. The noble Lord, Lord Hodgson, made that point during the Second Reading debate.</p><p>
            There will be several sources of this advice. They range from the regulator himself, through other information sources supported by the Government, such as Business Link, to the various social enterprise groups and professional advisers who specialise in this field. The Government are also engaged in wider work
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_340gc' title='Col. 340GC &mdash; HL Deb 25 March 2004 vol 659 c340GC' name='column_340gc' href='#column_340gc' rel='bookmark'>340GC</a>
